04/03/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- The Athens 2004 Olympic Organising Committee announced on Wednesday (3 March) the successful completion of the 4th World Press Operations briefing. The venue provided information and updates on the progress of preparations for the Summer Games to 210 members of the foreign press. The briefing started on Sunday and was attended by Australian Olympic Committee Vice President Kevin Gosper, who expressed satisfaction with the services provided to media representatives and commended the completion of the main press centre. (ANA - 03/03/04)
